[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This is OpenSpec, a lightweight specdriven development tool. Yes, another one of those developed by Fishian AI to solve the problem of spec tools losing requirements in chat history and using up too many tokens. But with so many other more popular'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'specdriven development tools out there like Amazon\'s Kira and GitHub\'s spec kit, is the simplicity of OpenSpec enough to make it worth your time? Let\'s find out. And before we do, don\'t forget to hit that subscribe button.'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Specdriven development turns your vague prompt into a clearly defined document with tasks for your AI agents to follow, massively reducing the amount of bugs and errors in your final project. Check'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'out this video by Andrew to learn more about the details. And OpenSpec makes the whole process so much simpler, narrowing things down to three major steps. Draft your proposal, review the tasks, then implement the tasks. In'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'fact, let\'s go ahead and see it in action. I want to create a fake LLM benchmarking tool. To do that, let\'s start off with a simple vit react project. Then in our project, we\'ll initialize openspec, which will ask us'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to select an AI tool. In my case, that will be open code. I\'ll hit enter. And now we should have a few new files. First, an agent.md file and an openspec folder. We\'ll talk more about this one'

